er=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 1862<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 4:52:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PoP counter-proposal based on simple principles</span><hr size=1> Given <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s understandable reluctance to define a role or vision for the magician class, prefering, perhaps impractically, that the players instead provide their own, the time has come for us to define our own <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Vision</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in order to communicate with the machine that generates the rules <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (Verant)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, that we might be better satisfied as customers.<br>
<br>
While I would never claim to speak for all magicians, I do carefully observe a variety of styles and preferences here in this forum and in play, and think I am qualified at least to expound my own vision, which should not be terribly alien to the readers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Gobaner:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  The principle reason I play a mage and not some other class is my boon companion <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  My warrior in a bottle, he kicks ass and takes names when I uncork him.  I want him to be powerful, I want him to win.  I want people around me to be glad they are on the same side.  He is my sword and shield in a hostile world.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> A thousand fiery blades:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  But even then, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is but a means to an end: holding off the enemy while I rain woe and ruination down upon.  I think you will die now.<br>
<br>
Those were the basic facts of magician life for quite some time.  Once upon a time, they were even both true.  This initial vision, however modified and made more complex, must remain the core of what it is to be a mage.  A mage is a classic, self contained group.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> melees the foe while I support him by buffing, healing, and nukes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Temporal Powers:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Many class abilities can be viewed from the perspective of affecting the pace of encounters: lengthening the fight through healing or mezzing, shortening the fight by dealing damage, buffs and debuffs, haste and slow, and so on.  Magicians are no exception.  The temporal powers given to us, besides pets and nukes above, include creating and redistributing mana using rods, call of the hero, damage shields, the malosini line, and various summons, especially focii.  This succinctly describes most of our spell set, and are the tools with which every mage works and becomes strong in.<br>
<br>
The question is, knowing this, what more might mages be offered with an additional five levels that would build on their strengths, preferring to modify old roles than establish new, especially unrelated roles.  In other words, how to preserve the class and thereby the customers who enjoy it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> New Pets:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Something like another circle beyond <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Greater Vocaration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  If they have special powers or cast spells, please do not make them stupid.  I would prefer fightings pets.  Elemental pets for 61-64, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Monster Summoning 4</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> at 65.  Give MS4 some power.  Damage shield.  The pets must keep pace with the mobs, and <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>not</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> be nothing more than a weak but mana efficient damage over time spell.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> A bigger nuke:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Obviously.  What ever nuke or nukes seems appropriate: a fire based bolt, a conjured based shock, and an evocation based rain.  A new nuke every other level.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> A bigger damage shield:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Single target DS somewhere 61-3, group DS 64-5.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Upgraded Self Buffs:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  One Upgrade each in the Arch Shielding, Elemental Aura, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>and</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Phantasmal Armor lines.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Upgraded Pet buffs:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  If not in the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Burnout Line</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, something else, like a mini-avatar that consumes a gem, perhaps as an AA skill.  Something: at least one combat related pet buff.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Summons:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Two summons.  A belt worth wearing, and weapon worth summoning.  Either one or both can be pet only.  If I have to have a stupid summons, let it be to summon a bag of caster wearable pajamas, with maybe a little stats or resists on them and low AC.  They can and should look dorky, marking the wearer as an obvious Corpse Recovery.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Malosini:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  If we want to be little creative, extending an existing role a little ways, how about a PBAoE <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Malosini</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Gives me something to do to aid enchanters, but requires some personal risk.  An upgrade to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Malosini</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
So how does what has been revealed on test go with this?<br>
<br>
New pets, check, except MS4, and who knows how good the pets will be?  If they suck, we suck.<br>
New nukes, but they aren't the right ones.  Back to the drawing board.<br>
Bigger damage shield, but group only.  Give us the targetted DS upgrade.<br>
Upgraded self buffs, but again, they aren't the right ones.  Too many archshields, too many elemental shields and those are weak, and no phantasmal upgrade.<br>
No pet buffs.<br>
No summons.<br>
Malosini upgrade okay, but I still want PBAoE Malosini too.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, they give us:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Mezz Summmoned:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I am not given easily to profanity, but WTF?  I do not know how to mezz.  Never, ever, in my darkest imaginings, did I ever consider that I might ever mezz anything ever.  Please god no.  I don't care how useful it might be, on one, two or more planes, but I do not care.  If you want me on crowd control, either give me PBAoE Malosini, to support the enchanters who already know how to mezz, or, if you insist on giving me a crowd control summoned spell, give me <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Root Summoned</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Now root is a spell that many magicians have coveted for years.  If we must have a new crowded control toy against summoned, let it be <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Root</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  Mages have been thinking about what they might do with root for a long time, and they would actually <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>enjoy</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> rooting, as opposed to mezzing.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Charmed Summoned:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I suppose it had to happen eventually, what with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Dire Charm</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and all, but I am not excited.  I will accept it if necessary.  But I tell you what, trade you charm and mezz summoned for PBAoE Malosini and Root Summoned, and you will have some happy mages.  Oh, and it had better be a damn good root too--summoned only.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Imbue Elements:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I do not care if I can sell them to tradeskillers for a thousand plat each, or you can use them with tailoring to make robes I can sell for 50K in bazaar, really, no thank you.  This is just eating up spells slots.  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>IF</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> we must have this, then I suggest the following.  Give this line <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>also</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to enchanters, but give mages enchant silver, electrum, gold, platinum, and steel, so we can enchant our metals for tradeskilling.  <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>IF</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> I am made into an imbuer for tradeskills, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>then</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> I want to be able to do something for myself to help myself skill up.  Otherwise, I would rather do without the imbuer role entirely.<br>
<br>
I make no stand as to the relative value of nukes, as the ultimate value of them depends on how good our pets are, which is unknown.  I understand that every class must now be a damage dealer in order to raid.  I do not want to become more like an enchanter.  Fix the numbers on the spells, and give me some pet support, and I will be a happy mage.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Sage ArchMage Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
