</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#333333>(9/22/02 12:49:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Agree</span><hr size=1> I think you have some good ideas here Raz. I definitely agree that VI should focus on improving our abilites rather than adding new ones. Looking at our spell lines, these are my thoughts:<br>
<br>
Pets:<br>
I dont worry about the epic pet getting useless. It will still be the strongest pet by far I think. I rather expect the new pets to have special abilites, and hope the fire pet will get some serious use again.<br>
Personally I would prefer if our major upgrade came through the new pets, rather than through<br>
<br>
<br>
Nukes:<br>
We have five spell lines of nukes:<br>
- Evocation based shock spells. These roughly double with each step, look at Blaze, Char, and now Sun Vortex. I think Sun Vortex is a reasonable upgrade.<br>
<br>
- Conjuration based shock spells. If you look at the proposed upgrade it is nowhere near the upgrade from SoSwords (44) to SoSteel (5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , then SoFB (60). Black Steel definitely needs some tuning to be a valuable upgrade, with 1200 damage it would be in line with its predecessors. If the manacost for Black Steel could be kept as it is now it would make it a good all day nuke.<br>
<br>
- Evocation based bolt spells. Taking a look at our spells again, the proposed upgrade is perfectly in line with the predecessors Lava Bolt and Seeking Flame. On the other hand our bolt spells always had an advantage in damage for the reduced easy of use, so Firebolt of Tallon might need an upgrade to make it worth using over the new shock spells. 1400-1500 damage? Seems ok.<br>
<br>
- Evocation based rain spells. Maelstrom of Thunder is a true upgrade damage wise, but the mana cost for it is much too high. If this could be reduced a bit I think the spell would be well balanced. 550-600 mana seems reasonable.<br>
<br>
- Anti summoned nukes. I dont think we need an upgrade here. Unless there are lots of summoned creatures and the spells would truly have an advantage in resists (which they dont have it seems).<br>
<br>
<br>
Debuffing:<br>
I love your idea of a PBAoE Malosini. Gets expensive manawise if you have many mobs there and want to support the chanter <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
However an upgrade to Mala / Malosini? Seeing this proposed and the number of lure spells for wizards it might well be neccessary, but I hope it wont.<br>
<br>
<br>
Damage shields. Do we need an upgrade here? Of course wouldnt say no to one, but I dont think thats of priority.<br>
<br>
<br>
And the other new toys?<br>
I really see no use in giving mages summoned mez, without giving them means to stop the angry mob if mez breaks (stun, root,...). Our pets wont always be able to help us out. For the same reason summoned charm is worthless, even more because of the one pet limit (of course if we were allowed to have two pets up then...this would be an entirely different story).<br>
And I again agree with Raz that imbue spells have no place in our book. Thats not what we do.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
