<br>
This does not 'change our role' but puts us more in line with how we should be.  We have always been imo the kings of vs summoned casters.  Necros being the same of undead.  Throughout the entire game necros have had undead only charm, undead only nukes, undead only slows, mez spells etc.  While none of them were as good as a enchanters, it gave them some utility while fighting a specific set of creatures.  I always wondered why mages didn't get similar.<br>
<br>
I, for one, would LOVE the new mez/charm spells.  Mez would come in VERY handy as solo i could handle multiple pulls, or add even more versitility to a group while fighting summoned creatures.<br>
<br>
This spell is no where near good enough to replace a enchanter with mez duty... Our role is not being redefined, we're gaining versatility vs a certain type of creature.<br>
<br>
You realize that when a mob is mezzed it IS rooted... It also doesn't attack anyone.  It also has a memblur effect... It also lasts for a specific amount of time (in this case 5 ticks or 30 seconds).  Root has always been dubbed 'ghetto mez' and rightfully so... Root doesn't have many uses aside from saving your ass when you don't have a pet up.  <br>
<br>
<br>
I do agree, however, that we should get a upgraded anti-summoned nuke... But NOT in the place of these VERY USEFULL spells.  The charm spell will almost guarantee us the chance to charm a better pet in some circumstances than what we can summon.  We gain the risk of having it break every 20.5 minutes... Ok, just mez and re-charm.  <br>
<br>
I WANT these spells, and they will IMPROVE my class.  If you get them nerfed or removed, personally i'll be very angry =P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucyricusbloodbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyricus Bloodbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 962<br> <font color=#333333>(9/23/02 4:36:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://520013139003-001.bei.t-online.de/IWD_Human_Male_Wizard3.gif height=58 width=36></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Since Black Steel was made public it was always Conjuration based. Do NOT believe Castersrealm - its the worst source of information ever, heh<br>
