<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  While I would never claim to speak for all magicians, I do carefully observe a variety of styles and preferences here in this forum and in play, and think I am qualified at least to expound my own vision, which should not be terribly alien to the readers.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Second paragraph, first post.  Sorry, can't figure out how to be any clearer than that.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Dilandu:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> A summoned only root spell has got to be about the most insane idea i've ever heard...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, it was just an idea, as I already said, based purely on an emotional appeal.  That is, I have heard many mages wish for root, and I think it would be fun.  I never thought of mages mezzing, nor have I ever heard any mage proposing that ability.  Given that, I thought it would be more <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>fun</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to play with a root, rather than a mezz.  I do understand that root is weaker than mezz.<br>
<br>
It is just one idea out of many, and it may not be a good idea.  But really, mezz?<br>
<br>
I still don't want to be like an enchanter.  I don't think many mages do.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Dilandu:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  You realize that when a mob is mezzed it IS rooted<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well duh.<br>
