<br>
I didn't make this up, and I don't agree that mages should have root.<br>
<br>
However, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> seems pretty insistant on giving us some form of elemental crowd control, and I put two and two together and got an idea.<br>
<br>
Seriously, how much would you pay in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bazaar</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> tomorrow for an <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Earring of Living Slime</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> if it were for sale?  And you can tell me that a lot mages do not want <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Root</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?<br>
<br>
All I did is try to forge a compromise between what <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> sees for us, and what at least some of us see for ourselves.  It was not a sin, nor was it the stupidest idea in the world <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (way too much competition for that)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Dilandu:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  This does not 'change our role' but puts us more in line with how we should be. We have always been imo the kings of vs summoned casters. Necros being the same of undead. Throughout the entire game necros have had undead only charm, undead only nukes, undead only slows, mez spells etc. While none of them were as good as a enchanters, it gave them some utility while fighting a specific set of creatures. I always wondered why mages didn't get similar.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is not unreasonable.  Of course if we had had those abilities previously, we would have been in an uproar over the lack of summoned mobs.  Presumably, there is at least one or two new zones with lots of elemental mobs, and ideally more zones with at least some summoned mobs.<br>
